            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "possible fix:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/memline.c b/src/nvim/memline.c\r\nindex 5839061aac..142c6ee4b2 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/memline.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/memline.c\r\n@@ -3934,7 +3934,7 @@ long ml_find_line_or_offset(buf_T *buf, linenr_T lnum, long *offp, bool no_ff)\r\n   if (buf->b_ml.ml_usedchunks == -1\r\n       || buf->b_ml.ml_chunksize == NULL\r\n       || lnum < 0) {\r\n-    return -1;\r\n+    return (lnum == 1) ? 0 : -1;\r\n   }\r\n \r\n   if (offp == NULL) {\r\n```\r\n\r\nBehavior of `line2byte(1)` is also affected (also in recent vim). but in that case only by completely unchanged buffer, i e inserting on line 1 is enough to return the valid value. ",
